               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1799">18th century</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance> The manuscript contains numerous supplications for a man, whose name
                     was erased and replaced by <persName ref="PRS15414WaldaM"/>. The second part of
                     the original supplicant’s name appears to be <foreign xml:lang="gez"
                        >ክርስቶስ፡</foreign>. There is a short ownership note mentioning <persName
                        ref="PRS15416AbtaGabr"/>, <persName ref="PRS15414WaldaM"/>, <persName
                        ref="PRS15424WalattaTsion"/>, <persName ref="PRS15425WalattaYoh"/>, and
                        <persName ref="PRS15426WalattaKidan"/> on <locus target="#1vb"/>, written by
                     a secondary hand. Two supplications for <persName ref="PRS15413GabraHeywet"/>,
                        <persName ref="PRS15415WalattaIya"/>, <persName ref="PRS15416AbtaGabr"/> and
                        <persName ref="PRS15417WalattaWanas"/> were written by the same hand as the
                     ownership note in <ref target="#a2"/>.</provenance>
               </history>
